  <section id="main" class="wrapper">
    <div class="inner">
      <h2>Project Overview</h2>
      <p>
        This project simulates the Microsoft Viva Engage environment using public Reddit data to evaluate community health
        in enterprise collaboration platforms. Our team built a dual-metric scoring framework‚ÄîCommunity Health Score (CHS)
        and Community Health Index (CHI)‚Äîto assess both quantitative engagement and qualitative sentiment.
      </p>

      <h2>Key Contributions</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Scraped and processed over 10,000 Reddit posts and comments using Python</li>
        <li>Built sentiment and empathy models with GPT to evaluate civility and tone</li>
        <li>Designed CHS and CHI scoring systems to track engagement and health signals</li>
        <li>Created interactive dashboards with Power BI for HR and community stakeholders</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Python (Pandas, NLTK, OpenAI API)</li>
        <li>Power BI</li>
        <li>Reddit API</li>
        <li>Prompt engineering for tone classification</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Key Insights</h2>
      <p>
        Our findings revealed that content quality (semantic depth, structure) had more impact on community health than volume alone.
        We successfully flagged "pseudo-active" groups with high activity but low empathy and relevance, enabling preemptive interventions
        by community managers.
      </p>

